_header: O beauteous branch flower of fumosity
_description: Poem to his mistress — eight stanzas rhyme royal

CamTCC599.First Lines:
[O] beauteous braunche flour of formosyteTo yow in countenance no
                    creature ys comparable…
CamTCC599.Last Lines:
…But Ihesu that our sauyour most excellent kyngMe in to your
                    presence hastyly he bryng
